An overview of ancient toreutic and archeological findings in Estonia; an introduction to the traditions of guild crafts , analysis of the work and products of local workshops. An overview of ethnographic  decorations, the history of alchemy, traditions related to metal from  mysticism to science history.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To introduce archaeological findings  from Estonia, guild handicraft, ethnographic ornaments and the history of alchemy as related to metals.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of  the course, students should: have an overview of the  ancient toreutics and archaeological findings in Estonia;  be able to analyse guild craft; know the differences  in the making of ethnographic decorations during different periods.
